      "body": "Saving non-\"final\" transactions is indeed something we may need to do eventually for a number of reasons, including smart contracty-ones. Might even be worthwhile to use in a non-backwards-conflicting way for things like multiple nlocktimed transactions that are stored for things like RBF bumping, so different logic can handle them instead of legacy. concept ACK",
